---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-28";
---

<Base title="Privacy — BoltMate" pathname="/privacy">
  <section class="section legal-section">
    <div class="container legal">
      <p class="eyebrow">PRIVACY</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <h2>Short version</h2>
      <p>
        BoltMate is a desktop utility that fans Logitech Bolt host-switch
        events across your devices and machines. The cross-machine sync
        is LAN-only — no host-switch event ever leaves your local
        network. We collect the minimum data needed to issue you a
        license and reply to your support requests.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Email + account profile.</strong> When you sign in via
          Apple or Google, your identity provider gives us your verified
          email address and (optionally) your display name. We bind your
          BoltMate license to that email.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>License + entitlement state.</strong> Each license row
          stores the email, OAuth subject identifier, tier (Trial /
          Boltmate), Stripe customer + checkout-session IDs once you
          purchase, issue and refund timestamps, and a salted SHA-256
          hash of a stable hardware identifier from the desktop app —
          which we use only to prevent the same machine from running
          multiple back-to-back free trials.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Support submissions.</strong> When you write to
          <a href="mailto:support@boltmate.app">support@boltmate.app</a>
          or use the in-app "Send logs" button, the email address you
          provided, your message, optional name, and any log bundle you
          attached are stored long enough to reply and resolve the
          issue.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payment metadata.</strong> Card details never touch
          our servers. Stripe handles checkout end-to-end; we receive
          customer ID + payment intent ID, plus webhook events for
          completion and refunds.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we do NOT collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Keystrokes, mouse movement, scroll, clicks.</strong>
          macOS calls the permission BoltMate needs "Input Monitoring,"
          but we use it solely to read HID++ host-switch frames from the
          Bolt receiver. The app never sees what you type.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage telemetry, analytics, third-party trackers.</strong>
          No Google Analytics, Plausible, Mixpanel, etc. on this site or
          in the app. No anonymous "feature usage" reports.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Host-switch event content.</strong> The cross-machine
          sync is LAN-only — UDP multicast + Bonjour-discovered TCP. No
          host-switch event is ever sent off your local network.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where data lives</h2>
      <p>
        Account, license, and refresh-audit data live in Microsoft Azure
        Cosmos DB in the East US 2 region. Support log bundles you
        upload land in Azure Blob Storage in the same region with an
        automatic 30-day delete lifecycle. Email is sent via
        <a href="https://resend.com/" rel="nofollow">Resend</a>.
        Authentication is brokered by Microsoft Entra External ID; your
        identity-provider credentials never touch us directly.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We never sell, rent, or syndicate your data. The processors that
        see narrow slices of it are listed above (Microsoft Azure for
        storage + auth, Stripe for payments, Resend for email,
        Cloudflare for DNS + email routing). Each is bound by their own
        data-protection terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You can request a copy of your license + account data or delete
        your account entirely by emailing
        <a href="mailto:support@boltmate.app">support@boltmate.app</a>
        from the address on your account. We complete deletion requests
        within 30 days; the only data that survives is what we're
        required to keep for tax + accounting reasons (Stripe transaction
        records).
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        BoltMate is run by Jared Allen. Reach us at
        <a href="mailto:support@boltmate.app">support@boltmate.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-section { padding-block: 64px 96px; }
  .legal { max-width: 720px; }
  .legal h1 {
    margin: 12px 0 0;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: #161616;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-weight: 660;
    font-size: 20px;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: #161616;
  }
  .legal p, .legal li {
    color: var(--bm-fg-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .legal p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .legal a.text-link, .legal a {
    color: var(--bm-green-deep);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .legal strong { color: #161616; font-weight: 620; }
  .updated {
    font-family: var(--bm-font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--bm-fg-tertiary);
    margin: 18px 0 28px;
  }
</style>
